but you're not a student here

194
00:12:45,766 --> 00:12:47,351
so I can't let you inside.

195
00:12:48,185 --> 00:12:50,687
Iju... I just came past to see Mr. Prezbo.

196
00:12:50,938 --> 00:12:52,272
Well, he's teaching right now.

197
00:12:52,814 --> 00:12:54,441
I know. I can wait.

198
00:12:55,692 --> 00:12:57,486
You're gonna have to stay outside.

199
00:12:57,569 --> 00:13:00,864
After the bell, I'll tell Mr. Pryzbylewski
you're out here for him, ok?

200
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,348
I'm going to surprise you with something.

201
00:13:14,211 --> 00:13:15,671
You already have.

202
00:13:16,046 --> 00:13:20,801
I got a tip from an informant
about a leak out of the grand jury unit.

203
00:13:20,884 --> 00:13:22,552
Sad to say it's checked out.

204
00:13:22,719 --> 00:13:25,555
- We know about the leak.
- But do you know who it is?

205
00:13:26,056 --> 00:13:27,599
Gary dipasquale.

206
00:13:28,558 --> 00:13:31,561
Decent enough guy but he's got
a bear of a gambling problem

207
00:13:31,645 --> 00:13:34,406
and a bank of drug lawyers
who are willing to pay for their look-sees.

208
00:13:34,648 --> 00:13:37,234
Troy Sanders, Marvin bronfman,

209
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:40,320
Dennis cray, sid silverstein.

210
00:13:40,529 --> 00:13:43,657
And the pick of the litter?
Maurice Levy.

211
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:46,118
I kid you not.

212
00:13:47,035 --> 00:13:48,328
Gary is their leak?

213
00:13:48,412 --> 00:13:51,581
He broke right away.
He was ready to give it up. Needed to.

214
00:13:53,583 --> 00:13:56,753
One-party consent call
implicating Maury Levy.

215
00:13:58,088 --> 00:14:00,215
- Where's Gary now?
- He went up to the second floor

216
00:14:00,298 --> 00:14:03,677
to hand in his letter of resignation and
went home to wait for the sword to drop.

217
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:04,803
He's okay.

218
00:14:05,929 --> 00:14:07,681
He's better than you'd think.

219
00:14:08,557 --> 00:14:12,811
You know, if we can turn Levy
and some of these other drug lawyers,

220
00:14:12,894 --> 00:14:15,439
we can route the drug money all over town.

221
00:14:17,107 --> 00:14:18,775
It's sad business, I know,

222
00:14:18,942 --> 00:14:21,028
but at least we know the truth now, right?

223
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:24,114
The truth, you say?

224
00:14:32,247 --> 00:14:33,290
Hey.

225
00:14:33,623 --> 00:14:34,958
Duquan, hello.

226
00:14:35,042 --> 00:14:36,293
- Snatch-pops.
- Hey!

227
00:14:36,376 --> 00:14:38,837
